[It is disgraceful that doctors and nurses have had to move from their homes to protect themselves. The consequence is not merely the disruption to their families from displacement, but also the fact that some health facilities were forced to close their doors as a result. Another distressing statistic is 132 attacks against medical units since this most recent Ebola outbreak began in Aug 2018, causing 4 deaths and 38 injuries among health workers and patients. Since August, a staggering number of children, 545 aged less than 18 years, have been infected. The global community must get behind the control effort to stop the outbreak. All the tools are at hand, but the population must be won over, clearly easier said than done, but new approaches must be put into action. - Mod LK]

- Wed 22 May 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
